document_notes.text:
This update for tar fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2022-48303: Fixed a one-byte out-of-bounds read that resulted in use of uninitialized memory for a conditional jump (bsc#1207753). 

Bug fixes:

- Fix hang when unpacking test tarball (bsc#1202436).

notes.text: GNU Tar through 1.34 has a one-byte out-of-bounds read that results in use of uninitialized memory for a conditional jump. Exploitation to change the flow of control has not been demonstrated. The issue occurs in from_header in list.c via a V7 archive in which mtime has approximately 11 whitespace characters.
